==English==

===Etymology===
Coined in 1910 by psychologist {{w|Henry H. Goddard}}, from {{der|en|grc|μωρός||foolish, dull}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈmɔːɹɒn/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɔːɹɒn|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|informal|derogatory}} A [[stupid]] person; an [[idiot]]; a [[fool]].
# {{lb|en|dated|originally}} A person of borderline intelligence in the former classification of mental retardation, having an intelligence quotient of 50-69.
#: {{syn|en|feeble-minded}}

====Usage notes====
The current medical term for having an IQ between 50 and 69 is “mild [[intellectual disability]]”.

